<html>

<head>
<title>Doug Bandow</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Doug Bandow</h1>

<p>Doug Bandow is a Senior Fellow with the <a
href="/revolution/by_name/C/Cato.html">Cato Institute</a>.</p>

<p>Bandow earned a B.S. in economics at Florida State University and
a J.D. at the Stanford Law School. He worked for Ronald Reagan's 1980
presidential campaign and served in Reagan's administration on the Office
of Policy Development.</p>

<p>Bandow writes prolifically for magazines and newspapers and is the author
of many books and policy papers. Among his areas of specialty are drug
legalization, noninterventionist foreign policy and the relationships between
religious faith and liberty.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.cato.org/main/bandow.html">
	http://www.cato.org/main/bandow.html</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li>none yet</li>
</ul>

