<head>
<title>Bob Bickford</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Bob Bickford</h1>

<p>Bob Bickford is the acting chair of the Libertarian Party of Marin
County, California. Bickford has been involved in the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a>
since the early 1980s, serving in county and state affiliates and being
a local representative for the
<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1988/">Paul</a> and
<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1992/">Marrou</a>
campaigns.</p>

<p>Bickford helped set up the Liberty Bell BBS, and later the
<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.well.com/conf/liberty/">Liberty conference</a>
on <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.well.com/">the Well</a>. He was webmaster for
the <a href="/revolution/living/oceania.html">Oceania project</a>
for a while, and currently maintains the <img src="/images/www.gif"
alt="[WWW]"><a href="http://www.well.com/conf/liberty/home.html">Liberty
Library</a>.</p>

<p>Bickford served as one of two State Coordinators for northern <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a>
for the <a href="/revolution/politics/napm.html">Not a Penny More</a>
campaign.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:rab@well.sf.ca.us">rab@well.sf.ca.us</a><br>
Web: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="http://www.well.com/~rab/">http://www.well.com/~rab/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li>none yet
</ul>

