<html>

<head>
<title>Buckeye Liberty Foundation</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Buckeye Liberty Foundation</h1>

<p>The Buckeye Liberty Foundation (BLF) in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/oh/">Ohio</a> is a nonpartisan,
nonprofit organization
whose goal is "to educate Ohioans about the benefits of individuals freedom
and the necessity of personal responsibility," according to their
introductory pamphlet. The Foundation advocates "public policy to cut taxes,
reduce government intervention, dissolve bureaucracy, increase individual
liberty and restore Constitutional law."</p>

<p>The BLF's activities include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Quarterly newsletter.</li>
<li>Educational pamphlets.</p>
<li>Market research into effective presentation of the ideas of liberty.</li>
<li>Legal action (when viable) to protect Constitutional guarantees.</li>
<li>Speakers Bureau.</li>
<li>Student scholarship essay contest (Buckeye Liberty Endowment).</li>
<li>Dinner meetings.</li>
</ul>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
1933 East Dublin-Granville Road #176, Columbus, OH 43229<br>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:buckeyelib@aol.com">buckeyelib@aol.com</a>.<br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/G/MatthewGaylor.html">Matthew Gaylor</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/">Politics</a></li>
</ul>

