<head>
<title>Harry Browne</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Harry Browne</h1>

<img src="HarryBrowne.gif" alt="" align=left>

<p>Investment author Harry Browne was the 1996
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a> candidate
for President of the United States. He has said he would run again in 2000
if the party is large enough and he still feels young enough.</p>

<p>Browne is an author, public speaker and investment advisor. His nine
books have sold over 2 million copies, and include four best sellers. His
books include <cite>How You Can Profit from the Coming Devaluation</cite>,
<cite>How I Found Freedom in an Unfree World</cite>, and <cite>You Can
Profit from a Monetary Crisis</cite>, as well as the recently released
campaign book <cite>Why Government Doesn't Work</cite>. Since 1974 he
has published the <cite>Harry Browne's Special Reports</cite> investment
newsletter.</p>

<br clear=all>
<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Harry Browne for President<br>
4094 Majestic Lane, Suite 240,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/va/Fairfax.html">Fairfax</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/va/">VA</a> 22033<br>
voice: 1-800-314-8611 or 714-437-7911<br>
fax: 714-432-1468<br>
e-mail: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:73030.3256@compuserve.com">73030.3256@compuserve.com</a><br>
WWW:  <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.HarryBrowne96.org/">http://www.HarryBrowne96.org/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><A href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1996/browne/">
	Harry Browne for President</a></li>
