<head>
<title>CWJ</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Committee for Waco Justice</h1>

<p>The Committee for Waco Justice is a small Washington, D.C.-based
organization of mainly libertarian members,
dedicated to bringing to justice federal officials responsible for the
<a href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/waco/">Waco
massacre</a>. Formed in late 1993, the group has conducted demonstrations
at the White House and the Justice Department on anniversaries of key
events in Waco, followed the House and Senate hearings, and has
generate numerous reports including a mass market paperback,
<cite>The Davidian Massacre</cite>.</p>

<p>Contact <a href="/revolution/by_name/M/CarolMoore.html">Carol Moore</a>
or:</p>
<address>
Committee for Waco Justice<br>
Box 65518, Washington, DC 20035<br>
voice: (202)635-3739 or (202)797-9877<br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/M/CarolMoore.html">
	Carol Moore</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/waco/cwj.html">
	Committee for Waco Justice forms</a></li>
<li><a
href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/waco/reaction/cwj_protest.html">
	CWJ protests at BATF headquarters</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/waco/reaction/signs.html">
	Police steal protest signs</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/waco/trial/cwj_file.html">
	CWJ files complaints</a></li>
</ul>

