<head>
<title>CPSR</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Computer Professionals for Social Responsibility</h1>

<p>Computer Professionals for Social Responsibility (CPSR) is an organization
supporting online freedom and privacy. CPSR actually began in 1981 as a group
of individuals opposing computer-controlled nuclear launches, i.e. a nuclear
attack without human intervention. CPSR later broadened their agenda to include
such issues as encryption.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.cpsr.org/home/">http://www.cpsr.org/home/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/E/EFF.html">
	Electronic Frontier Foundation</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/express/techno/crypto/clipper/petition.html">
	Anti-Clipper petition</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/legal/police/">
	Police and police powers</a></li>
</ul>

