<head>
<title>DPF</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Drug Policy Foundation (DPF)</h1>

<p>The Drug Policy Foundation (DPF) is an organization
promoting open debate on alternatives to the drug war, including
decriminalization, legalization and medical solutions. DPF publishes
the quarterly <cite>Drug Policy Letter</cite>.</p>

<p>The DPF has an impressive Board of Directors, led by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/T/ArnoldTrebach.html">Arnold Trebach</a>,
the <a href="/revolution/by_name/A/ACLU.html">ACLU's</a> Ira Glasser,
the <a href="/revolution/by_name/H/Hoover.html">Hoover Institute's</a>
<a href="/revolution/by_name/M/JosephMacNamara.html">Joseph MacNamara</a>,
Ethan Nadelmann, <a href="/revolution/by_name/S/KurtSchmoke.html">Kurt
Schmoke</a>, and federal judge Robert Sweet. DPF's Board of Advisors
includes <a href="/revolution/by_name/C/Cato.html">Cato's</a> <a
href="/revolution/by_name/B/DavidBoaz.html">David Boaz</a>, <a
href="/revolution/by_name/N/NORML.html">NORML's</a> Richard Cowan,
Lester Grinspoon, Carl Sagan and <a
href="/revolution/by_name/S/ThomasSzasz.html">Thomas Szasz</a>.

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
4455 Connecticut Ave. NW, Suite B-500<br>
Washington, DC 20008-2302<br>
voice: (202) 537-5005<br>
fax: (202) 537-3007<br>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:dpf@dpf.org">dpf@dpf.org</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/aclu.html">
	ACLU, others call for investigation of feds</a></li>
<li><A href="/revolution/politics/orgs.html">
	Libertarian-interest political organizations</a></li>
</ul>

