<html>

<head>
<title>Ken Gaillot Jr.</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Ken Gaillot Jr.</h1>

<p>Ken Gaillot Jr. is a Libertarian activist in Pensacola Beach,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/">Florida</a>.</p>

<p>Gaillot re-activated the College Libertarians at Louisiana State
University in 1987, serving as Chair until 1990 and remaining an active
member until graduating in December 1991. Also while at LSU, Gaillot
co-edited an alternative magazine, <cite>The Wonderland Times</cite>, and
coordinated precinct walking for Libertarian Michael Wolf's 1991 <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/la/">Louisiana</a> State Senate
campaign.</p>

<p>Gaillot lived in Montgomery County,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/">Texas</a> from
January 1992 to August 1994, during which time he re-activated the
<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lptx/lpmc/">Libertarian Party
of Montgomery County</a> and served as its Chair.</p>

<p>Since September 1994, Gaillot has lived in the Pensacola, Florida
area. He currently maintains the <a href="/revolution/"><b>Revolution</b></a>
web site.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:scimitar@scimitar.com">scimitar@scimitar.com</a><br>
Web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.gulf.net/~ken/">http://www.gulf.net/~ken/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lptx/lpmc/">
	Libertarian Party of Montgomery County, Texas</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lptx/lpmc/proposal.html">
	Proposal to form Montgomery County chapter</a></li>
</ul>

