<head>
<title>ISIL</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>International Society for Individual Liberty</h1>

<p>The International Society for Individual Liberty (ISIL) is one of the
prime movers of the modern libertarian movement. ISIL was formed with the
merger of the Society for Individual Liberty (SIL) and Libertarian Internatinal
(LI).</p>

<p>The original SIL was started in 1969, and can lay claim to being the
first libertarian organization to spring from the modern libertarian
movement.</p>

<p>ISIL publishes the <cite>Freedom Network News</cite> and a series of
position papers, both available on their Web site.
ISIL runs Freedom's Forum Bookstore, which sells a wide selection
of libertarian books and publishes books under the name of Cobden Press.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
1800 Market St.,
<A href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/SanFrancisco.html">San
Francisco</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">CA</a> 94102<br>
Phone: 415-864-0952<br>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:71043.2711@compuserve.com">71043.2711@compuserve.com</a><br>
Web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.isil.org/">http://www.isil.org/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/M/VinceMiller.html">Vince Miller</a></li>
