<html>

<head>
<title>David Koch</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>David Koch</h1>

<p>David Koch, one of the heirs to the Koch Industries family fortune, won the
1980 <a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a>
nomination for Vice President. Koch's financial
contributions to the campaign helped the Libertarian Party in its
impressive third-party showing of nearly one million votes that year.</p>

<p>Koch, born in 1940, was an all-American basketball center at MIT. At the
time of the 1980 election, he was corporate president of Koch Industries Inc.,
which had $8 billion in sales in 1979.</p>

<p>David Koch's brother Charles also became active in the libertarian movement,
funding several libertarian organizations including the <a
href="/revolution/by_name/C/Cato.html">Cato Institute</a>.</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1980/">
	1980 Libertarian campaigns</a></li>
</ul>

<hr>

<p>Sources:</p>
<ul>
<li>Buck, Rinker. "How Those Libertarians Pay Their Bills." <cite>New
York</cite>, 3 November 1980, 13:18.
</ul>

