<head>
<title>Marijuana Policy Project</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Marijuana Policy Project (MPP)</h1>

<p>Founded in January 1995 by
<a href="/revolution/by_name/K/RobKampia.html">Rob Kampia</a>
and Chuck Thomas, the Marijuana Policy Project (MPP) is a lobbying
organization trying to implement various specific proposals to
lessen the penalties for marijuana crimes. Email or write to them
with your street address to receive a free brochure.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
P.O. Box 77492, Capitol Hill, Washington, D.C. 20013<br>
General information: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:info@mpp.org">info@mpp.org</a><br>
Other: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:MPP@mpp.org">MPP@mpp.org</a><br>
<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.mpp.org/">http://www.mpp.org/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/K/RobKampia.html">Rob Kampia</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/body/drugs/rights/enforce/clubs.html">
	Cannabis Buyers' Clubs supply medical marijuana</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/body/drugs/online/">
	Online drug resources</a></li>
</ul>

