<head>
<title>Carol Moore</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Carol Moore</h1>

<p>Carol Moore is a co-founder of the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/C/CWJ.html">Committee for Waco Justice</a>
and is active with the
<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpdc/">Libertarian Party of
the District of Columbia</a>. Moore once described herself on LPUS as a
"libertarian non-violent pacifist decentralist pagan hippy communalist
worshiper of the goddess maryjane" who can be "sometimes bad tempered,
but working on that."</p>

<p>Moore authored <cite>The Davidian Massacre</cite>, a
stunning book on the extent of the government's evil in Waco.
The book was published in 1995 by Gun Owners of America
(1-800-417-1486). Disk versions of book should be available from Moore.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Box 65518-CM, Washington, D.C. 20035<br>
voice: (202) 635-3739<br>
<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:cmoore@CapAccess.org">cmoore@CapAccess.org</a><br>
</address>

