<head>
<title>Tonie Nathan</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Tonie Nathan</h1>

<p>Theodora "Tonie" Nathan was the
<A href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party's</a> first
vice presidential
candidate (in 1972) and was the first woman ever to receive an electoral vote,
predating Geraldine Ferraro by over a decade. She is still an active
Libertarian activist in Oregon.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:tonie@efn.org">tonie@efn.org</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/M/RogerMacBride.html">Roger MacBride</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1972/">
	1972 Libertarian campaign</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpor/campaign96.html">
	November 1996 Oregon elections</a></li>
</ul>

