<head>
<title>P.J. O'Rourke</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>P.J. O'Rourke</h1>

<p>Patrick J. O'Rourke is a libertarian humorist. His books include
<cite>Republican Party Reptile</cite>, <cite>Modern Manners</cite>,
<cite>Holidays in Hell</cite>, <cite>Parliament of Whores</cite> and
<cite>Give War a Chance</cite>.</p>

<p>O'Rourke was the editor of <cite>National Lampoon</cite> in the late 1970's.
His classic articles in that magazine include "A Long, Thoughtful Look Back
at the Last Fifteen Minutes" and "How to Drive Fast on Drugs While Getting
Your Wing-Wang Squeezed and Not Spill Your Drink."</p>

<p>O'Rourke's work has since appeared in many other magazines, including
<cite>Playboy</cite>, <cite>Esquire</cite>, <cite>Car and Driver</cite>,
<cite>Vanity Fair</cite>, <cite>Parade</cite> and <cite>Rolling
Stone</cite>.</p>

<p>The <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.web-presence.com/mac/pjhome.shtml">P.J. O'Rourke
Unofficial Home Page</a> has a biography and excerpts from various
writings and speeches.</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/commerce/transportation/humor/">
	Planes, trains and automobiles</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/famous.html">
	Famous Libertarians</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/humor/hitchhiker.html">
	Democrat hitchhiker</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/quotes/govt.html">
	Quotes on government</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/quotes/parties.html">
	The American political system as pi&ntilde;ata</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/community/welfare/quotes.html">
	Quotes on welfare</a></li>
</ul>

