<html>

<head>
<title>Ron Paul</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Ron Paul</h1>

<p>Ron Paul was the 1988 presidential candidate of the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a>.
Paul had previously served four terms as a Republican U.S. Congressman,
switching to the Libertarian Party after he lost the Republican
Senate nomination to Phil Gramm.</p>

<p>In 1996, Paul switched back to the Republican Party, and ran successfully
for his old Congressional seat. He defeated the incumbent Republican in
the primary and Democratic and Libertarian challengers in the general
election. Although he ran and won as a Republican, he specifically
did not resign his Libertarian Party membership.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:75372,2537@compuserve.com">75372,2537@compuserve.com</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1988/">
	1988 Libertarian campaigns</a></li>
</ul>

