<html>

<head>
<title>Murray Rothbard</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Murray Rothbard (1926 - 1995)</h1>

<p>Murray N. Rothbard was one of the founders of the modern libertarian movement
and of the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a>.</p>

<p>Rothbard's <cite>Libertarian Manifesto</cite> was one of three books
defining early libertarian philosophy, the other two being
<a href="/revolution/by_name/N/RobertNozick.html">Nozick's</a>
<cite>Anarchy, State and Utopia</cite> and
<a href="/revolution/by_name/H/JohnHospers.html">Hospers'</a>
<cite>Libertarianism</cite>.</p>

<p>Rothbard was S.J. Hall Distinguished Professor of Economics at the
University of Nevada, Las Vegas, and Vice President for Academic Affairs
of the <a href="/revolution/by_name/L/Mises.html">Ludwig von Mises
Institute</a> in Auburn,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/al/">Alabama</a>.</p>

<p>After Rothbard's death, the February 1995 <cite>Libertarian Party
News</cite> published <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.lp.org/lp/lpn/9502-Rothbard.html">"Murray Rothbard: 1926 -
1995"</a> in his memory.</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/body/health/clinton.html">
	Criticism of Clinton's health care proposal</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/philosophy/books.html">
	Books on libertarian philosophy</a></li>
</ul>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
