<html>

<head>
<title>J. Neil Schulman</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>J. Neil Schulman</h1>

<p>J. Neil Schulman is a Libertarian science fiction author and gun rights
activist (not to be confused with Libertarian science fiction author and
gun rights activist <a
href="/revolution/by_name/S/LNeilSmith.html">L. Neil Smith</a> --
no, I'm not kidding).</p>

<p>Schulman is the author of the Prometheus award-winning novels
<cite>Alongside Night</cite> and <cite>The Rainbow Cadenza</cite>,
as well as a wide array of other material from the CBS Twilight Zone episode
"Profile in Silver" to the nonfiction <cite>Stopping Power: Why 70
Million Americans Own Guns</cite> and <cite>Self Control Not Gun
Control</cite>. He also writes extensively for newspapers and magazines.</p>

<p>Some of his books are available online, including
<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.pulpless.com/stopower.html"><cite>Stopping Power</cite></a>
and <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.pulpless.com/hein.html"><cite>The Robert Heinlein
Interview and Other Heinleiniana</cite>.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
P.O. Box 94, Long Beach, CA 90801-0094<br>
Voice mail and fax: (500) 44-JNEIL<br>
email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:jneil@pulpless.com">jneil@pulpless.com</a><br>
web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.pulpless.com/jneil/">http://www.pulpless.com/jneil/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/science/books/sf.html">
	Libertarian science fiction</a></li>
</ul>

