<head>
<title>Joseph Schumpeter</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Joseph Schumpeter</h1>

<p>Joseph Schumpeter was a free-market economist. He is the originator of
the term "creative destruction" as a description of how competition improves
the economy even as it destroys obsolete firms and ideas.</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/commerce/economic/process/biblio.html">
	Market process bibliography</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/commerce/economic/books/kirzner.html">
	Notes on Kirzner's <cite>Competition and
	Entrepreneurship</cite></a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/commerce/economic/books/schumpeter.html">
	Notes on <cite>Capitalism, Socialism and Democracy</cite></a></li>
</ul>

