<html>
<head>
<title>Rick Tompkins</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>Rick Tompkins</h1>

<p>Rick Tompkins is an activist with the
<A href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpaz/">Libertarian Party of
Arizona</a>. Tompkins unsuccessfully ran for the 1996
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a> nomination
for President.</p>

<p>Tompkins became active in the Libertarian Party of Arizona in 1988,
and ran for the U.S. Senate in that year. Tompkins has served four terms
as Chair of the Arizona LP. Tompkins is also involved with the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/F/FIJA.html">Fully Informed Jury
Association</a>. He was once listed by the Republican Liberty Caucus
as "coordinator" for Arizona, but without his knowledge or permission.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Rick Tompkins, Libertarian for President<br>
8129 N. 35th Avenue, #2-262, Phoenix, AZ 85051<br>
Voice: 602-930-1268<br>
Fax: 602-930-1739<br>
E-mail: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:tompkins@nguworld.com">tompkins@nguworld.com</a><br>
Web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.nguworld.com/rick96/">http://www.nguworld.com/rick96/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
