<head>
<title>Chris Whitten</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Chris Whitten</h1>

<p>Economist Chris Whitten, a former Managing Editor for <a
href="/revolution/by_name/L/LaissezFaire.html">Laissez Faire Books</a>, now
operates Free Market Enterprises (FME), an Internet presence consulting firm.
As FME, Whitten maintains the <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.free-market.com/">free-market.com</a> Internet site.</p>

<p>During his college years, Whitten studied Austrian economics under <a
href="/revolution/by_name/K/IsraelKirzner.html">Israel Kirzner</a> at
New York University, founded NYU's Classical Liberal Organization,
and interned at the <a href="/revolution/by_name/C/Cato.html">Cato
Institute</a> as a Charles Koch Fellow. Whitten obtained his B.S. in
economics in 1993.</p>

<p>Whitten was Laissez Faire Books' Managing Editor from 1993 to 1995, when
he left Laissez Faire to start his own Internet presence consulting firm,
Free Market Enterprises.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Free Market Enterprises<br>
314 East 70th Street 2C<br>
New York, NY  10021<br>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:Chris@free-market.com">Chris@free-market.com</a><br>
Web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.free-market.com/ciw.html">
	http://www.free-market.com/ciw.html</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li>none yet
</ul>

