<head>
<title>Phil Zimmermann</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Phil Zimmermann</h1>

<p>Phil Zimmermann is the creator of Pretty Good Privacy (PGP), a strong
encryption program. Zimmermann lived for three years under the threat of
prosecution by U.S. federal pigs for providing privacy with teeth.
Zimmermann is represented by attorney Phil DuBois.</p>

<p>Send donations to:</p>
<address>
the Zimmermann Legal Defense Fund<br>
c/o, Phil DuBois, 2305 Broadway, Boulder CO 80304<br>
Phone: 303-444-3885<br>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:dubois@csn.org">dubois@csn.org</a> or
	<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:zldf@clark.net">zldf@clark.net</a><br>
</address>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
Email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:prz@acm.org">prz@acm.org</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/express/techno/crypto/pgp/pgp.html">
	The story of PGP</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/express/techno/crypto/pgp/closed.html">
	US closes investigation, won't prosecute PGP creator</a></li>
</ul>

