<head>
<title>FEE</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Foundation for Economic Education</h1>

<p>The Foundation for Economic Education (FEE), founded by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/R/LeonardRead.html">Leonard Read</a> in
1946, is the oldest active libertarian organization.</p>

<p>FEE publishes <cite>The Freeman</cite>, a scholarly magazine on
free-market economics. FEE also publishes books and pamphlets, and holds
seminars.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
30 S. Broadway, Irvington-On-Hudson, NY 10533<br>
email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:freeman@westnet.com">freeman@westnet.com</a><br>
voice: 914-591-7230<br>
web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.fee.org/">http://www.fee.org/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/R/LeonardRead.html">Leonard Read</a></li>
