<head>
<title>LP-Maryland Fundraising</title>
<!-- Place: Maryland (USA) -->
<!-- Time: March 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>LP-Maryland Fundraising</h1>

<p>March 10, 1995, from <a
href="/revolution/by_name/M/JesseMarkowitz.html">Jesse Markowitz</a>:</p>

<p>The Maryland Libertarian Party recently completed a major membership drive. 
Our drive consisted of a letter to all of our recent prospects, our expired
members and our current members.  The letter and inserts were designed and
produced by the Monticello group.  This was a <em>very</em> successful 
mailing.  We had an overall response rate of over 10%, and received just over
$4.00 for every dollar we spent on the mailing.</p>

<p>These memberships have all been forwarded to National, and should be
recorded during the month of March.  There were over 75 memberships. I can't
tell how many National memberships were new as opposed to renewals, so I can't
tell you how our membership numbers will change on the March listings. 
However, I do expect they will go up!</p>

