<head>
<title>Quotes on Political Parties</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Quotes on Political Parties</h1>

<hr>
<h2>O'Rourke on the American Political System</h2>

<p>The American political system is like a gigantic Mexican Christmas
fiesta. Each political party is a huge pi&ntilde;ata -- a
papier-mach&eacute; donkey, for example. The donkey is filled with full
employment, low interest rates, affordable housing, comprehensive medical
benefits, a balanced budget and other goodies. The American voter is
blindfolded and given a stick. The voter then swings the stick wildly in
every direction, trying to hit a political candidate on the head and
knock some sense into the silly bastard.</p>

<p>-- <a href="/revolution/by_name/O/PJORourke.html">P.J. O'Rourke</a>,
in <cite>Parliament of Whores</cite></p>

<hr>
<h2>Teddy on the Two-Party System</h2>

<p>The old parties are husks, with no real soul within either, divided on
artificial lines, boss-ridden and privilege-controlled, each a jumble of
incongruous elements, and neither daring to speak out wisely and
fearlessly on what should be said on the vital issues of the day.</p>

<p>-- Theodore Roosevelt</p>

<hr>
<h2>On Affiliation</h2>

<p>I am not a member of any organized political party. I am a Democrat.</p>

<p>-- Will Rogers</p>

