<head>
<title>Libertarian Science Fiction</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Libertarian Science Fiction</h1>

<p>Winners of the Prometheus Award for Libertarian Science Fiction,
presented by the Libertarian Futurist Society:</p>

<ul>
<li><p>1995: <cite>The Stars are Also Fire</cite>, by Poul Anderson;
Hall of Fame Award: <cite>The Star Fox</cite>, by Poul Anderson.</p>

<li><p>1994: <cite>Pallas</cite>, by L. Neil Smith; Hall of Fame Award:
<cite>We</cite>, Yevgeny Zamiatin.</p>

<li><p>1993: <cite>The Multiplex Man</cite>, by James P. Hogan; Hall of Fame
Award: <cite>The Dispossessed</cite>, by Ursula K. Le Guin.</p>

<li><p>1992: <cite>Fallen Angels</cite>, by Larry Niven, Jerry Pournelle, and
Michael Flynn; Hall of Fame Award: <cite>This Perfect Day</cite>, by Ira
Levin.</p>

<li><p>1991: <cite>In The Country of the Blind</cite>, by Michael Flynn;
Hall of Fame Award: <cite>An Enemy of the State</cite>, by F. Paul Wilson.</p>

<li><p>1990: <cite>Solomon's Knife</cite>, by Victor Koman;
Hall of Fame Award: <cite>Healer</cite>, by F. Paul Wilson.</p>

<li><p>1989: <cite>Moon of Ice</cite>, by Brad Linaweaver; Hall of Fame Award:
<cite>Alongside Night</cite>, by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/S/JNeilSchulman.html">J. Neil Schulman</a>.</p>

<li><p>1988: <cite>The Jehovah Contract</cite>, by Victor Koman; Hall of Fame
Award: <cite>The Stars My Destination</cite>, by Alfred Bester.</p>

<li><p>1987: <cite>Marooned in Realtime</cite>, by Vernor Vinge; Hall of Fame
Award: <cite>Stranger in a Strange Land</cite>, by Robert A. Heinlein,
and <cite>Anthem</cite>, by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/R/AynRand.html">Ayn Rand</a>.</p>

<li><p>1986: <cite>Cybernetic Samurai</cite>, by Victor Milan;
Hall of Fame Award: <cite>The Syndic</cite>, by Cyril Kornbluth,
and <cite>Illuminatus!</cite>, by Robert Shea & Robert Anton Wilson.</p>

<li><p>1985: None of the Above (i.e. no award); Hall of Fame Award:
<cite>The Great Explosion</cite>, by Eric Frank Russell,
and <cite>Trader to the Stars</cite>, by Poul Anderson.</p>

<li><p>1984: <cite>The Rainbow Cadenza</cite>, by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/S/JNeilSchulman.html">J. Neil Schulman</a>;
Hall of Fame Award: <cite>1984</cite>, by George Orwell,
and <cite>Fahrenheit 451</cite>, by Ray Bradbury.</p>

<li><p>1983: <cite>Voyage from Yesteryear</cite>, by James P. Hogan;
Hall of Fame Award: <cite>Atlas Shrugged</cite>, by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/R/AynRand.html">Ayn Rand</a>, and
<cite>The Moon Is a Harsh Mistress</cite>, by Robert A. Heinlein.</p>

<li><p>1982: <cite>The Probability Broach</cite>, by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/S/LNeilSmith.html">L. Neil Smith</a>.</p>

<li><p>1979: <cite>Wheels Within Wheels</cite>, by F. Paul Wilson.</p>

</ul>

<p>For more information about the Libertarian Futurist Society, write
89 Gebhardt Road, Penfield, NY 14526, or contact the editor of its
journal <cite>Prometheus</cite>, Anders Monsen (<img src="/images/mail.gif"
alt="[EMAIL]"><a href="mailto:amonsen@aol.com">amonsen@aol.com</a>).</p>

