<head>
<title>Firearms and Crime</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Firearms and Crime</h1>

<p>One of the most common reasons for gun ownership is as a deterrent to
crime. Gun grabbers claim that guns cause crime rather than deter it.
Where do the facts stand? Read on.</p>

<p>The obsolesence of self-defense is one of the great myths of our time.
Police forces were never meant to, don't and are <a href="protect.html">unable
to supersede</a> self-protection.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="home.html">Crime deterrent vs. household danger</a>
<li><a href="mostused.html">Firearms most used in crime</a>
<li><a href="japan.html">An American gangster in Japan</a>
<li><a href="defense/">Examples of self-defense</a>
</ul>

