<head>
<title>The Politics of Firearms</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>The Politics of Firearms</h1>

<p>Efforts at gun control are misguided or even totalitarian in intent.
Gun control proponents often resort to <a href="grabbers.html">perpetuating
myths and lies</a> to gain support.</p>

<p>Gun owners should prefer <a href="lvr.html">Libertarians over Republicans</a>
based on principle and pragmatism.</p>

<p>Gun grabbers like to parade around a few police chiefs and other law
enforcement officials to demonstrate their support for each new round
of gun control. Survey after survey, however, has found that the vast
majority of police support gun ownership and oppose gun control.</p>

<p>Granted, many of these surveys are not scientific, and I don't
particularly care what any government official thinks of my inherent
and inalienable rights. However, gun grabbers routinely and purposely
perpetuate a myth that cops support gun control, and they don't.</p>

<p>Most police support individual firearm ownership, as evidenced by</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="mack.html">Arizona Sheriff Refuses to Enforce Brady Bill</a>
<li><a href="lelobby.html">Law Enforcement Lobby Supports Gun Rights in
California</a>
<li><a href="ales.html">American Law Enforcement Survey Reveals Gun Rights
Support</a>
<li><a href="pba_ga.html">Georgia Police Survey Reveals Gun Rights Support</a>
<li><a href="pba_ss.html">Southern States Police Survey Reveals Gun Rights
Support</a>
<li><a href="police.html">Police Magazine Survey Reveals Gun Rights Support</a>
</ul>

