<head>
<title>Congress Investigates Feds' Abuses</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: July 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Congress Holds Hearing (Again) Into Federal Agents' Abuses</h1>

<p>Beginning July 12, 1995, for the first time <a href="congress.html">since
1980</a>, the U.S. Congress held hearings on abuses by federal police.</p>

<p>The U.S. House of Representatives' joint subcommittee of the
Judiciary and Government Reform and Oversight committees is investigating
government tactics that led to deaths at <a href="waco/">Waco</a> and
<a href="rubyridge/">Ruby Ridge</a>. Reps. Bill McCollum (R-FL) and Bill
Zeliff (R-NH) chair the joint subcommittee, and scheduled hearings for
mid-July.</p>

<p><a href="rubyridge/aftermath.html">Senate hearings</a> into the Ruby Ridge
incident were held in September 1995.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
