<head>
<title>ATF Overkill</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: July 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>ATF Gets Military Firepower</h1>

<p>Never known for its delicate style, the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and
Firearms in July 1995 received 22 OV-10D aircraft from the Department of
Defense.</p>

<p>Each OV-10D, capable of speeds up to 300 mph, is outfitted with two 
7.62mm M-60C machine guns, each posessing 500 rounds, and carries
one Sidewinder missle under each wing, along with Snakeye bombs, rocket
packages, cluster bombs and fire bombs.</p>

<p>The ATF says nine of the aircraft will be unarmed and used only for
surveillance, and that the others will be used for spare parts. Uh huh.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
