<head>
<title>Victoria, Texas Militia</title>
<!-- Place: Victoria, Texas (USA) -->
<!-- Time: August 1994 -->
</head>

<body>
<h1>The Victoria Militia</h1>

<p>The August 7, 1994
<A href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/SanAntonio.html">San
Antonio</a> <cite>Express-News</cite> reported on the
forming of a militia in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/Victoria.html">Victoria</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/">Texas</a> by about a dozen
residents "fed up with gun control."</p>

<p>Local authorities supported the militia's right to bear arms and defend
liberty, but cautioned them not to break the law. "A militia by its very
nature is constitutional; a vigilante group is not," said Lt. Tom Eastland,
head of the Victoria Police Department's crime prevention unit, according to
the <cite>Express-News</cite>.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
