<head>
<title>Northwest Florida Militia</title>
<!-- Place: Santa Rosa County, Escambia County and Okaloosa County,
	Florida (USA) -->
<!-- Time: May 1994 -->
</head>

<body>
<h1>The Northwest Florida Militia</h1>

<p>In 1994, three Florida Panhandle counties established militia as a sign of
protest against gun control, and specifically the assault weapons ban.</p>

<p>As reported in the <cite>New York Times</cite> in May 1994, the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/SantaRosa.html">Santa
Rosa</a> County Commission unanimously established a militia comprised of
every able-bodied man, woman and child. County commissioners will distribute
membership cards and wall plaques to people wanting to make a statement
of support for gun rights.</p>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/Escambia.html">Escambia</a>
and
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/Okaloosa.html">Okaloosa</a>
counties followed suit not long after. Escambia,
Santa Rosa and Okaloosa counties are <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/">Florida's</a> westernmost
counties, making up a good portion of the "Panhandle" area.</p>

<p>Jim Barnett is a leader in the northwest Florida militia, and believes the
Second Amendment exempts militia members from gun control laws such as the
assault weapon ban. Barnett owns Gateswood Sports Inc., a guns, archery and
fishing store north of Pensacola.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
