<head>
<title>Militia Rally in Tallahassee</title>
<!-- Place: Tallahassee, Florida (USA) -->
<!-- Time: February 12, 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>The Rally in Tally</h1>

<p>From John S. Burns Sr., 813-369-5273:</p>

<p>In January of 1994 a local talk show host, Mike Willy, in the Orlando,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/">Florida</a> area
made an 'off the wall comment' in response to a call
concerning upcoming Anti-gun legislation in Florida.</p>

<p>"Well lets hold a demonstration in Orlando."</p>

<p>Another caller immediately replied, "Hell! Let's march on
<A href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/Tallahassee.html">Tallahassee</a>!"</p>

<p>Three short weeks later on Abraham Lincoln's birthday, February 12, 1994,
thousands of people converged on the state capitol steps for --</p>

<hr>

<h2>The Shot Heard Round The World - Part II</h2>

<p>In spite of posturing by current and would be politicians, One message
rang loud and clear, and was best summed by one sign which read --</p>

<p>"We Come Unarmed, THIS TIME!"</p>

<p>This was not a Rally about family values, or outcome based education,
of abortion, or welfare, or of taxes, although all of these subjects were
discussed.</p>

<p>This was not a gathering of any political party, or of any political
action group, though many were well represented by their members.
This was instead, The Armed Militia of The Great State of Florida,
as defined in title 10, section 311 of the Code of the United States,
Called to it's sacred duty, the defense of the Constitution of the
United States of America, against <em>all</em> enemies, Foreign and
domestic, and the defense of the rights and civil liberties guaranteed under
it.</p>

<p>Now let this message go across this great country - <em>we will march on
Washington!</em> And we formally request the assistance and accompaniment of
the Militias of our 49 sister states and the U.S. territories.</p>

<p>Gather your friends and relatives. And meet us in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/dc/">Washington D.C.</a> to
deliver this message - We are free men, And we will <em>stay that way</em>!
<em>All</em> gun control legislation will be stopped and repealed!</p>

<p>To coordinate with the people in your state and area contact...
John Gutmacher, 305-760-7505; Philip Curtis, 813-984-3933;
Dan Gonzales, 813-936-2827; or Mike Willy, 407-628-4104.
For computer files contact Wayne Steinard at 813-984-1618.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
