<head>
<title>Militiaman, License Plate and Death</title>
<!-- Place: near Frazeysburg, Ohio (USA) -->
<!-- Time: June 28(?), 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>'Militiaman' Killed By Cop</h1>

<p>Michael H. Hill, 50, replaced his
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/oh/">Ohio</a> license plate
with a home-made one
reading "Militia." Needless to say, this was not considered acceptable
behavior by the local police.</p>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/oh/Frazeysburg.html">Frazeysburg</a>,
Ohio Sgt. Matt May stopped Hill's car a little after 2am
because it had no state license plate. Hill came out, was asked to get back
inside. He did, and drove away. May followed Hill for a few miles, when Hill
stopped again. This time Hill came out with a .45-caliber handgun, at which
point the officer shot and killed him.</p>

<p>Although police have received a few threatening phone calls, local militia
leaders are cooperating with law enforcement to defuse the situation. Gary
Long of the Southeastern Ohio Defense Force militia said he did not know Hill.
"There is no animosity between the militia and law enforcement around here,"
he said. "We work with them."</p>

<p>This incident points up the amalgam of views that make up the modern militia
movement. For the most part, militias are a new phenomenon, attracting people
who haven't previously been very active politically or ideologically. These
new people tend to be moderate conservatives or libertarians, often
religious, and in general average people.</p>

<p>But the militia movement has also attracted remnants of previous and
contemporary movements. Hill apparently comes from the "county movement,"
which rejects all authority above the level of the county. County-movement
advocates reject license plates, drivers' licenses and such.</p>

<p>To survive as a viable movement, militias must more precisely define
themselves ideologically. Militias have done a good job of rejecting racism
and violence. Now they must offer a positive vision of what they do support.</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: Associated Press article posted to Libernet.</p>

