<head>
<title>Firearms Used In Crime</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Firearms Used In Crime</h1>

<p><cite>USA Today</cite> published a full page graphic of the
most popular "crime guns" as reported by the Bureau of Alcohol
Tobacco and Firearms. Only one so-called assault weapon
is on the list and it is number 9:</p>

<ol>
<li>Smith & Wesson .38 Special Revolver
<li>Raven Arms .25 caliber
<li>Davis P-380
<li>Smith & Wesson .357 Revolver
<li>Ruger .22 caliber
<li>Lorcin L-380
<li>Smith & Wesson semiautomatic handgun
<li>Mossberg 12 gauge shotgun
<li>Tech DC-9
<li>Remington 12 gauge shotgun
</ol>

<p>Any numbers from BATF are suspect, both because BATF has an agenda to push
and because states don't uniformly report crime statistics to the federal
government. Nonetheless, the info above is useful, if taken with a grain of
salt.</p>

