<head>
<title>Books on Waco</title>
<!-- Place: Waco, Texas -->
<!-- Time: February - April 1993 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Books on Waco</h1>

<p>Many books have been published on the <a href="index.html">government
attack on the Branch Davidians</a> at Waco, Texas in 1993.</p>

<dl>
<dt><cite>The Ashes of Waco: An Investigation</cite>, by D.J. Reavis.
<dd>An journalist's investigation into the Waco affair. The book's
<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://rampages.onramp.net/~djreavis/">Web site</a> includes
an excellent overview with excerpts, Congressional testimony,
pictures and sound clips.</dd>
<p>
<dt><cite>The Davidian Massacre</cite>, by
<a href="/revolution/by_name/C/CarolMoore.html">Carol Moore</a>.</dt>
<dd>Written by a libertarian supporter of the Davidians, this book
systematically analyzes evidence that agents of the Bureau of Alcohol,
Tobacco and Firearms (BATF) and the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI)
committed real crimes against the Branch Davidians, including firing
first, firing from helicopters, sabotaging negotiations, lying to
the Attorney General and starting the fire that ended the siege.</dd>
</dl>

