<head>
<title>Antimilitia Law</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: introduced May 2, 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Antimilitia Law Proposed</h1>

<p>On May 2, 1995, H.R. 1544 was introduced to ban militia-style
organizations.</p>

<p>The proposed Domestic Insurgency Act of 1995 prohibits the formation of
private paramilitary organizations. According to the text of the bill,</p>

<blockquote>
<p>(a) whoever knowingly participates in a paramilitary organization shall be
fined under this title or imprisoned not more than 10 years, or both.</p>

<p>(b) as used in this section, the term paramilitary organization "means two
or
more individuals acting together, organized in a military or paramilitary
structure, who knowingly - </p>

<ol>
<li>possess firearms, explosives, incendiary devices, or other weapons or
techniques capable of causing injury or death to individuals, or
<li>provide or participate in training in the use of any such weapons or
techniques, with the intention that such weapons or techniques be used
unlawfully to oppose the authority of the United States or of any State or
for any other unlawful purpose.
</ol>
</blockquote>

<p>Note the "or" between the two definitions of paramilitary organization. The
first definition is broad enough to include steak knives, so essentially this
bill would prohibit anyone from organizing "in a military or paramilitary
structure," which is not defined.</p>

