<head>
<title>Pennsylvania CCW</title>
<!-- Place: Pennsylvania (USA) -->
<!-- Time: account from 1994, 1997 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Concealed-Carry Weapons (CCW) Permits</h1>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/pa/">Pennsylvania's</a>
Constitution states, "The right of the citizens to bear arms
in defence of themselves and the State shall not be questioned," (Article 1,
Paragraph 21). Permits to carry concealed firearms are available to someone who
goes down to the County courthouse with $12.50 and two passport sized photos of
himself, fills out a form, gets fingerprinted, and supplies two character
references. (In January 1997, someone emailed me to say that fingerprints
are not required.)</p>

