<head>
<title>Waco Could Have Been Peaceful</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Waco Could Have Been Peaceful</h1>

<p>The BATF could have served a search warrant or arrest warrant on the
Branch Davidians without incident.</p>

<p>Many years earlier, an argument between Davidian leaders resulted in
guns being fired. Koresh and the Davidians cooperated with local police in
resolving the matter.</p>

<p>Had the BATF wanted to arrest Koresh, they could have easily done so
when Koresh took his daily jog, or went into town for errands. But the BATF
had no crimes with which to charge Koresh; they used a search warrant as the
pretext for their military raid.</p>

<p>David Koresh offered to have the BATF inspect his weapons to ensure
their legality. The BATF ignored his request, instead plotting a military
assault.</p>

<p>Koresh knew the BATF was planning to raid the Davidians, and said as much
to the BATF's undercover informant. Despite this knowledge, the BATF went
ahead with their military assault.</p>

