<head>
<title>IRS Harrasses Waco Survivors</title>
<!-- Place: Houston, Texas (USA) -->
<!-- Time: reported December 1993 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>IRS Harrasses Waco Survivors</h1>

<p>Hotel owner Mark Domangue wanted to help survivors of the government's
brutal assault at
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/Waco.html">Waco</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/">Texas</a>,
so he allowed several surviving Branch Davidians
to stay at his hotel, in exchange for helping him with odd jobs.</p>

<p>The IRS <em>seized</em> the Brittney Hotel, claiming that Domangue should
have collected federal withholding and unemployment taxes from people, like the
Davidians, who paid for their rooms by working odd jobs.</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: AP story (appeared in December 15, 1993 Conroe, <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/tx/">Texas</a>
<cite>Courier</cite>).</p>

