<head>
<title>Waco Agents Rehired</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: on leave September 1993;
	fired October 28, 1993;
	appeled October 31, 1993;
	rehired January 9, 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>ATF rehires agents fired over Waco</h1>

<p>The Treasury Department's report on Waco blamed agents Phillip Chojnacki
and Chuck Sarabyn for the disaster. The two agents were placed on temporary
leave in September 1993 and were fired on October 28, 1993.</p>

<p>The two agents appealed on October 31, and under a settlement with the
BATF, received full back pay and benefits, had the incident removed from their
personnel files and returned to work in new roles January 9, 1994.</p>

