<head>
<title>Waco Survivors Plant Trees</title>
<!-- Place: Waco, Texas (USA) -->
<!-- Time: February 28, 1995 -->
</head>

<body>
<h1>Waco Survivors Plant Trees at Disaster Site</h1>

<p>March 1995, from <a href="/revolution/by_name/M/CarolMoore.html">Carol
Moore</a>:</p>

<p>A half-dozen Davidian survivors, a half-dozen supporters and about 30 people
from the press gathered on the Mt. Carmel property -- behind the fence -- for
the planting of six trees for the six Davidians who died February 28, 1993. 
They will plant 76 trees on April 19th for those who died that day.  To
contribute to the tree fund (and/or to get their literature list) send checks
to Mount Carmel Survivors Memorial Fund, Box 120, Axtel, TX 76624,
817-754-2146.</p>

