<head>
<title>Libertarian Activism: Strategy and Tactics</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: contemporary -->
</head>
<body>

<h1>Libertarian Activism: Strategy and Tactics</h1>

<p>Sometime around 1991, Libertarian activist
<a href="/revolution/by_name/I/TomIsenberg.html">Tom Isenberg</a> began
a series of tips, tactics, strategies, and case studies that became
known as "Tom's Tips" and proved invaluable to activists across
the country trying to learn how to grow their parties and run
campaigns. This web page has grown from that effort and now includes
articles from many people.</p>

<p>The premier resource for Libertarian activists is the outstanding
newsletter <cite>Libertarian Volunteer</cite>, edited by LP Communications
Director <a href="/revolution/by_name/W/BillWinter.html">Bill Winter</a>.
It is simply the best newsletter in the libertarian movement. It is
written for LP volunteers, activists, officers, and candidates. If you are
one of those, send your request to Bill Winter to get on that mailing
list.</p>

<h2>Issue Activism</h2>

<ul>
