<head>
<title>Libertarian Products</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Libertarian-Interest Products</h1>

<h2>LP T</h2>

<p>The ever-thoughtful activists of the Libertarian Party of Dallas County are
providing high-quality T-shirts, white on blue, with the LP name and Statue of
Liberty logo on the front and the national 800 number on the back. Limited
quantities of these T-shirts are now available for $15, which includes
first-class postage.  Contact Odis Ellis at (214) 690-1127.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Campaign Software</h2>

<p>Personal Campaign Manager for Windows Version 1.01<p>

<p>Minimum configuration: Microsoft Windows 3.1,
2 Megabytes of Hard Disk space + 2 Megabytes per 8000 voter names,
2 Megabytes of Memory,
IBM compatible 286 processor or above.</p>

<p>To order a copy of Personal Campaign Manager for Windows today, or to 
receive further information, call: 1-800-YOUR-PCM</p>

<hr>

<h2>Flags</h2>

<p>You can order the <cite>First Navy Jack</cite>, <cite>Culpepper</cite>, and
<cite>Gadsden</cite> "Don't Tread on Me" flags from Fuffin Flags, 241 Alexander
St. NW. Crawfordville, GA., 30631.  3'x5' cotton is $32.  3'x5' polyester is
$15.</p>

<p>The 'Betsy Ross' flag (13 stars in a circle in a blue field with 13
stripes.</p>

<p>The 'Bennington' flag (13 stars arranged in a blue field with 11 of them in
an arch within which is the number 76, and the remaining 2 stars in the top
corners of the field, and 13 stripes).</p>

<p>The 'Gadsden' flag (bright yellow with a coiled rattlesnake in the middle
under which boldly reads in black; "DONT TREAD ON ME".</p>

<p>The 'Navy' version of the 'Gadsden' (13 stripes, no field, with an uncoiled
rattlesnake in the middle under which boldly reads in black; "DONT TREAD ON
ME".</p>

<p>The flag of the Culpeper Minutemen (white flag with a ribbon design near
the top which reads in black; "THE CULPEPER MINUTE MEN", below which is a
coiled rattlesnake and on either side of which reads in black; "LIBERTY OR
DEATH", below which reads in black; "DONT TREAD ON ME."</p>

<p>If you can't find them near you, there's an excellent source for all kinds
of flags that does care ALL of the above flags in both the 3' * 5' size as
well as the small 4" * 5.5" desktop size. Here's the information:</p>

<pre>
THE FLAG SHOP

Miami - Bayside
(305) 530-1682

St.Louis - Union Station
(314) 421-3335

Baltimore - Harbor Place
(410) 625-2212

Ft. Lauderdale - Sawgrass Mills
(305) 846-1255
FAX: (305) 846-1266

<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/il/Chicago.html">Chicago</a>
	 - North Pier
(312) 321-8282

<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/il/Chicago.html">Chicago</a>
	 - Gurnee Mills (708) 855-1515

<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/pa/Philadelphia.html">Philadelphia</a>
	 - Franklin Mills
(215) 281-2720

Atlantic City - Ocean One Mall
(609) 344-0035
FAX: (609) 344-0910
</pre>

<p>Paul Nanson (<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:think@netcom.com">think@netcom.com</a> or
pdn@vnet.ibm.com [business related]).</p>

<hr>

<h2>Privacy and Surveillance</h2>

<p>My name is Michael Enlow. I am a retired private/legal investigater
and author of several books regarding private investigation/electronic
surveillance technology.</p>

<p>I wish to extend my services to the Internet to share and exchange
information on security and privacy protection issues. We are making
a lot of very informative info available <em>free</em> on the Internet. This
includes back issues of my newsletter "Inside Secrets", my 
schematics and plans, resources, guides, and other information.</p>

<p>For details, e-mail <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:INFO@ENLOW.COM">INFO@ENLOW.COM</a>  or anonymous FTP to
ENLOW.COM or <img src="/images/ftp.gif" alt="[FTP]"><a
href="ftp://ftp.enlow.com/">FTP.ENLOW.COM</a>.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Exploration of Democracy</h2>

<p>August 1994, from Tom Kindig (<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]">
<a href="mailto:tokind@kazak.NMSU.Edu">tokind@kazak.NMSU.Edu</a>:</p>

<p>I have uploaded to the SimTel Software Repository (available by anonymous
ftp from the primary mirror site OAK.Oakland.Edu and its mirrors):</p>

<p>SimTel/msdos/windows3/</p>

<p>wtp3_0.zip      We the People, exploration of democracy Win3.1</p>

<p>We the People is an exploration of democracy through famous documents
related to democracy, a study in constitutional forms of government, and
an examination of human rights laws around the world.</p>

<p>This product includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>a translation of the Magna Carta,
<li>Declaration and Resolves of the First Continental Congress,
<li>the Articles of Confederation,
<li>the Declaration of Independence,
<li>the complete US. Constitution,
<li>the U.N. Declaration of Human Rights,
<li>the complete constitutions of <a
href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/China/">China</a>, Iran, Germany, and <a
href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/Japan/">Japan</a>
<li>excerpts from the constitutions of
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/Canada/">Canada</a>,
	Chile,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/Europe/France/">France</a>,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/India/">India</a>,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/Mexico/">Mexico</a>,
	Nicaragua, and the Philippines.
</ul>

<p>US History students will appreciate the collection of important documents
leading to the Independence of the United States. The complete US
Constitution includes all articles, the Bill of Rights, and amendments
through 27, hypertext linked for side-by-side comparison.</p>

<p>Students of government may use the US., German, Chinese, Iranian, and
Japanese constitutions as a basis for comparing constitutional forms of
government.</p>

<p>People who are interested in Human Rights issues will find twelve
constitutions and the UN. Declaration of Human Rights as examples of
human rights ideals around the world.</p>

<p>Includes over 5800 search terms. Supports annotation and the use of
bookmarks.  All materials are presented in attractive TrueType(TM) fonts.
All may be printed or copied.</p>

