<head>
<title>Political Online Resources</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Online Resources for Libertarian Politics</h1>

<hr>

<h2>Web sites</h2>

<ul>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.libertarian.com/wwlp/">World Wide Libertarian Pages</a>:
an excellent collection of directories for online libertarian businesses,
organizations, parties and individuals</li>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.free-market.com/">Free-Market.com</a>:
"a starting point for liberty on the Internet;" free monthly lottery.</li>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://w3.ag.uiuc.edu/liberty/libweb.html">LibWeb</a>: nice collection
of libertarian information, including ISIL and Libertarian Alliance
pamphlets</a>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.mit.edu:8001/activities/libertarians/libertarians/www/lscwn.html">
College Libertarian Groups</a>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.buller.se/USR/MARCUS.WENDEL/">Marcus Wendel's eclectic
	catalog</a> of political web sites including libertarian pages</li>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.freedom-server.co.uk/Economic-Education.html">collection
	of Freeman essays</a></li>

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.vuse.vanderbilt.edu/~suerkeck/liberty.html">Libertarian
	Link</a>: a well-organized collection of links to
	libertarian resources of all kinds</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Discussion groups and electronic mail</h2>

<ul>

<li><a href="libernet.html">LIBERNET and LIBERNET-D mailing lists</a>

<li>LIBERNET is archived at <img src="/images/ftp.gif" alt="[FTP]"><a
href="ftp://think.com/pub/libernet">think.com</a>
and <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://pasture.ecn.purdue.edu/~laird/MLists/">Purdue</a>

<li><a href="lpus_ml.html">LPUS mailing list</a>

<li><a href="moderated.html">libertarian news and online resources</a>
	moderated mailing lists</li>

<li>Joe Dehn maintains a <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.rahul.net/dehnbase/liberml/">list of libertarian
	mailing lists</a> including local ones</li>

<li><a href="clinton.html">Clinton Administration E-mail directory</a>

<li><p><img src="/images/news.gif" alt="[USENET]"><a
href="news:talk.politics.libertarian">talk.politics.libertarian</a>: discussion
group for libertarian politics (should be renamed
rambling.philosophy.libertarian)</p>

</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Miscellaneous</h2>

<ul>

<li><a href="bbs.html">List of Libertarian BBSes</a>

<li><img src="/images/ftp.gif" alt="[FTP]"><a
href="ftp://ftp.demon.co.uk/pub/doc/liberty/">Libertarian Alliance
and FOREST Pamphlets</a> (FOREST is the Freedom Organisation for the Right to
Enjoy Smoking Tobacco; both organizations are British)

<li>The <img src="/images/gopher.gif" alt="[GOPHER]"><a
href="gopher://gopher.internet.com:2100">Electronic Newstand</a> has excerpts
from a number of good political magazines, including
<a href="/revolution/by_name/R/Reason.html"><cite>Reason</cite></a>,
the <cite>New Republic</cite> and <cite>Policy Review</cite>.</p>

</ul>

