<body>

<h1>Libertarian Campaigns</h1>

<ul>
<li><a href="1996/">1996</a>: Browne for President.</li>
<li><a href="1995/">1995</a>: More local victories.</li>
<li><a href="1994/">1994</a>: Libertarians elected in local and state
races across the U.S.</li>
<li><a href="1993/">1993</a>: Libertarians elected in local races in
New York, Pennsylvania and Alabama.</li>
<li><a href="1992/">1992</a>: Marrou for President.</li>
<li><a href="1988/">1988</a>: Paul for President.</li>
<li><a href="1984/">1984</a>: Bergland for President.</li>
<li><a href="1980/">1980</a>: Clark for President.</li>
<li><a href="1978/">1978</a>: First Libertarian elected.</li>
<li><a href="1976/">1976</a>: MacBride for President.</li>
<li><a href="1972/">1972</a>: Hospers for President.</li>
</ul>

