<html>
<head>
<title>FAQs and Related Resources</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1><a href="index.html">Tips for Libertarian Activists</a></h1>
<h2>FAQs and Related Resources</h2>
<p>Last updated 11/27/96 by
<a href="/revolution/by_name/I/TomIsenberg.html">Tom Isenberg</a></p>

<p>Here are some FAQs and other resources to help you answer questions and
assist with your research.  If you have a libertarian web site of your
own, you may want to include these links.  If you find other links that
should be here, please email
<a href="/revolution/by_name/I/TomIsenberg.html">me</a>.</p>

<p>As far as I can tell, the web still lacks a comprehensive libertarian
FAQ, one that has short but compelling answers to tough questions on all
aspects of libertarian theory and policy proposals, complete with
footnotes.  That this doesn't already exist is a crying shame, given the
many libertarian thinktanks, books, and the excellent scholarship that
is going on worldwide. Ideally, such a site might even allow people to
submit questions and/or answers that could then be incorporated into the
FAQ. If you have the talent and the dedication to develop and maintain
such a site, the world needs you at least as much as a good five-cent
cigar.</p>

<p>The following links are a good start for such a compilation, and I
congratulate and thank the folks who developed them ...</p>

<h3>FAQs</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.libertarian.org/libfaq.html">FAQ About
	Libertarianism (Paul Schmidt)</a>
<li><a href="http://www.batnet.com/liberty/liberal/Libertarianism.html ">Liberals &amp; Libertarians (Glenn Raphael)</a>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.ncl.ac.uk/people/chris.holt/home.informal/lounge/politics/libertarianism.html">Libertarianism (Eric Raymond)</a>
<li><a href="http://www.net-link.net/~briand/hubenrebuttal.html">Rebuttal
	to "Non-Libertarian FAQ" (Brian Carnell)</a>
</ul>

<h3>Documents</h3>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.self-gov.org/freeman/freeman.htm"><cite>Freeman</cite>
	articles online</a>
<li><a href="http://www.creative.net/~star/pamph.htm">ISIL Pamphlets</a>
<li><a href="http://www.lp.org/program/">Libertarian Party Program</a>
<li><a href="http://www.lp.org/platform/">Libertaian Party Platform</a>
<li><a href="http://www.digiweb.com/igeldard/LA/">Liberty Alliance</a>
<li><a href="http://www.shu.edu/~kellytra/polrsc.html">Ultimate Political
	Resource List</a>
</ul>

<h3>(Re)search Engines</h3>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.free-market.com/search.html">Free-Market.Com Search</a>
<li><a href="http://www.libertarian.com/bin/lwais.cgi">WWW.Libertarian.Com
	Search</a>
</ul>

<h3>Miscellaneous</h3>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.mackinac.org/askthe.htm">Ask the Economist!</a>
</ul>

