<head>
<title>Bureaucratese</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Our Cabbage Who Art in D.C.</h1>

<p>The Lord's Prayer is 66 words, the Gettysburg Address is 286 words,
there are 1,322 words in the Declaration of Independence, but government
regulations on the sale of cabbage total 26,911 words.</p>

<p>-- from the October 24, 1994 <cite>National Review</cite></p>

