<html>

<head>
<title>LPUS Electronic Mailing List</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: present -->
</head>

<body>
<h1>LPUS Mailing List</h1>

<p>October 1996 introductory message from
<a href="/revolution/by_name/D/JoeDehn.html">Joe Dehn</a>,
from the administrator of the LP-US mailing list:</p>

<h2>PURPOSE</h2>

<p>The LPUS echo/list is dedicated to discussion of
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a>
business at the national level.  It is expected that the content will
primarily be of interest to committee members, officers, staff, and
contractors of the national LP and its state affiliates, but any LP
activist, member, or even non-member is welcome to participate as long
as comments are constructive and on-topic.</p>

<p>LP "business" means matters pertaining to the LP as an organization.
Messages about political theory, about libertarian approaches to public
policy questions, about other libertarian organizations, or about
activities of interest to libertarians in general belong in
<a href="libernet.html">Libernet/Libernet-D</a>/LIBERTY.  Please do not
post newspaper articles
unless they relate specifically and directly to a matter that is 
itself on-topic.</p>

<p>"National level" means that messages should pertain to the national LP,
to the relationship between the national LP and its affiliates, or to
matters that would be of interest to LP organizations anywhere in the
U.S.; messages about topics of purely local concern (i.e., within one
state) should not be posted here.</p>

<h2>CATEGORY SYSTEM</h2>

<p>In order to facilitate the selection of messages by users who may not
be interested in following all of the discussion on all topics, each
LPUS message is assigned to a "category" as follows.</p>

<ul>
<li>LPUS: news and announcements of overall interest
<li> LPUS-PRES: presidential campaign
<li>LPUS-CAMP: campaigns (other than presidential)
<li>LPUS-PLAT: platform amendments
<li>LPUS-WWW: World Wide Web site operations
<li>LPUS-MISC: discussion that does not fit into specialty categories
</ul>

<p>Categories are assigned primarily on the recommendation of the user
posting the message; however the list owner reserves the option to
change the category of any message.</p>

<p>Users receiving LPUS messages via the Internet may specify which
categories are included in their subscriptions, except that the main
"LPUS" news and announcements category will be sent to all subscribers.
By default, subscriptions will include all categories except LPUS-PLAT
and LPUS-WWW.</p>

<p>Each message is posted under one category only, i.e., no "cross-posting"
across categories.  All subscribers receive the basic "LPUS"
distribution of news and announcements, so there is no need to post
those items again under another category in order for them to be
discussed.  If you have information that everybody <em>really</em> needs to
see, it probably belongs in the "LPUS" category.  Otherwise, if you
have something to say about more than one topic please post separate
messages focused on each topic, to allow subscribers to concentrate on
the aspects which interest them.</p>

<p>Detailed description of each category:</p>

<h3>LPUS</h3>

<p>News and announcements relating to the Libertarian Party overall.
Discussion of items posted here should be conducted under one of
the other categories.</p>

<p>Examples of appropriate messages:</p>

<ul>
<li>announcements and reports from national officers and committees
<li>news from the national office
<li>news about legislation that would affect party business (e.g.
          ballot access, campaign finance)
<li>corrections and updates to previous messages in this category
</ul>

<h3>LPUS-PRES</h3>

<p>News and discussion relating to the Libertarian presidential and
vice-presidential campaigns.</p>

<h3>LPUS-CAMP</h3>

<p>News and discussion relating to Libertarian campaigns for public
office <em>other</em> than president/vice-president.  As this is a national
forum, messages should relate in some way to the interests of a
national readership, in one or more of the following ways:</p>

<ul>
<li>messages about campaign techniques and procedures of general
         applicability nationwide
<li>messages about campaigns of national prominence
<li>messages which illustrate an issue or problem that is likely to
         be of interest to people working on other campaigns
 </ul>

<p>The following types of messages should <em>not</em> be posted:

<ul>
<li>announcements of local campaign meetings or appearances
<li>internal discussion of plans or problems of a specific campaign
</ul>

<h3>LPUS-PLAT</h3>

<p>Proposals for amending the national Platform.  This is intended
to provide for consideration of actual concrete wording, not for
abstract discussion of libertarian concepts.  Participants should
be familiar with the Platform.</p>

<h3>LPUS-WWW</h3>

<p>Discussion of WWW sites for LP organizations -- issues of site
construction and maintenance, helping people to establish new
sites, ideas and tools for improving existing sites.</p>

<h3>LPUS-MISC</h3>

<p>Discussion of any topic relating to the national LP organization
or to LP organizations nationwide <em>other</em> than those for which
there is a separate specialty category.</p>

<p>Examples of appropriate topics:</p>

<ul>
<li>matters relating to the LNC or the national office
<li>techniques for state and local party organization
<li>campaigns for internal party offices
</ul>
      
<p>Note: Although LPUS-MISC is "MISC", remember that it is still "LPUS".
This category is not intended as a general libertarian discussion
forum -- all messages should still meet the basic LPUS criteria of
"LP business" and "national".</p>

<h2>RELATED LISTS</h2>

<p>Several states now have mailing lists for discussion of LP business at
the state or local level.  For further information, check with your
state party or consult the list of libertarian mailing lists, which is
available via WWW at
"<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><A href="http://www.rahul.net/dehnbase/liberml/">http://www.rahul.net/dehnbase/liberml/</a>"
and as
"Libertarian FAQ: Mailing Lists" (archive-name: libertarian/mailing-lists).</p>

<h2>CROSS-POSTING</h2>

<p>Please do not cross-post announcements to Libernet and LPUS unless they
are important and urgent.  Please do not cross-post comments to
Libernet-D and LPUS unless they contain important followup information
(e.g., corrections, updates) relating to messages that previously
appeared in both places.  LPUS subscribers who want to receive general
libertarian announcements should subscribe to Libernet.  LPUS
subscribers who want to participate in a general libertarian
discussion/debate should subscribe to Libernet-D.  Please respect the
desires of individuals who <em>don't</em> want to receive such types of
messages by utilizing each forum for its intended purpose.</p>

<h2>INTERNET ACCESS</h2>

<p>LPUS is available via the Internet as a mailing list. Mailing list
subscribers may elect to receive their messages one at a time (i.e., as
soon as available) or in "batches" approximately twice per day. (A
batch contains several LPUS messages sent as one e-mail message, with
just one set of Internet headers.) If they do not otherwise specify,
CompuServe users will receive batches, other subscribers will get
messages one at a time.</p>

<p>Users may additionally specify which categories they wish to receive.
Users who receive messages one at a time may request any combination
of categories (except that the main "LPUS" category is always included.)
A limited form of this option is available to batch subscribers:
the categories that are included with a default subscription all
appear in one batch, but the categories that are only included by
request (LPUS-PLAT and LPUS-WWW) are batched separately.  Batch
subscribers will not receive such batches unless they specifically 
request those categories.</p>

<p>To subscribe, to change your category selection, or to cancel your
subscription, send a request to:</p>

<p><img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a href="mailto:LPUS-request@dehnbase.fidonet.org">LPUS-request@dehnbase.fidonet.org</a></p>

<p>To post a message, send to:</p>

<p>category@dehnbase.fidonet.org</p>

<p>where "category" is the category you believe best fits your message.
For example, to post a general announcement, sent your message to
"LPUS@dehnbase.fidonet.org"; to post a comment about the presidential
campaign, send to "LPUS-PRES@dehnbase.fidonet.org".</p>

<h2>FIDONET ACCESS</h2>

<p>LPUS is available to Fidonet users as an echo. Sysops should set access
to the area as seems appropriate to them based on the description above
and the nature of their BBS; if the system has many non-libertarian
users, it may be best to allow access only to LP members or by request,
to avoid extraneous traffic being generated by people who are not
familiar with the topic.</p>

<p>Fidonet BBSs carrying LPUS will receive all categories.  Users posting
a message should indicate the category by putting the category name
(e.g., "LPUS-PRES") in the Fidonet "To" field.  Messages without a
valid category name, including messages addressed to "All", will be
considered to be in category LPUS-MISC.</p>

