<title>1995 Elections</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: November - December 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>1995 Election Results</h1>

<p>Over seventy-five Libertarians ran in campaigns in at least twelve
states, with at least five winning. Due to the nature of the off-year
elections, most of the races were nonpartisan.</p>

<p>Winning campaigns:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpwa/sanders.html">Richard
	Sanders</a>,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/wa/">Washington</a>
	State Supreme Court.</li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpga/vanburen.html">Bruce
	Van Buren</a>, Avondale Estates, <a
	href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ga/">Georgia</a>,
	City Commission.</li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpga/methaney.html">Dewayne
	Methaney</a>, <a
	href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ga/Auburn.html">Auburn</a>,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ga/">Georgia</a>,
	City Commission.</li>
<li>Doug Carlsten, Brighton City,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/co/">Colorado</a>,
	City Council.</li>
<li>Jack Darragh, Pierce County,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/wa/">Washington</a>,
	Charter Review Commission. 6,100 votes (55%).</li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lppa/kreider.html">Alan
	Kreider</a>,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/pa/Spring.html">Spring
	Township</a>,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/pa/">Pennsylvania</a>,
	Supervisor. Appointed to fill vacancy.</li>
</ul>

<p>Other campaigns included:</p>
<ul>
<li>Dan Cochran, 49.5% for Loveland, <a
	href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/co/">Colorado</a>,
	Home Rule Commission, and 20.2% for Loveland, <a
	href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/co/">Colorado</a>,
	City Council</li>
