<p>In addition, eighteen Libertarians ran for public office in the town
of Windham, <a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ct/">Connecticut</a>,
including:</p>
<ul>
<li>John Adamo, 21% for School Board
<li>William Rood, 14.4% for the Board of Finance
<li>Charlie Ferris, 12.8% for Zoning Board of Appeals
<li>Stanley Viens, 11.2% for Selectman
<li>Shirley Vigneri, 10.8% for Zoning Board of Appeals
<li>Marvin Edelman, 10.8% for School Board
<li>Theodore Misak, 10.3% for Board of Finance
</ul>

<hr>

<p>Sources: November 15, 1995 Advisory from the Libertarian Party;
January 1996 <cite>Libertarian Party News</cite>;
March 21, 1996 Advisory from the Libertarian Party.</p>

