<html>

<head>
<title>'94 Elections</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: November 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>1994 Election Results</h1>

<p>Summary: seven Libertarians elected, three re-elected. Some disappointments
including the reduction of the <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/">New Hampshire</a>
legislative delegation from four to two.</p>

<p>Winning Libertarians:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/G/DonGorman.html">Don Gorman</a>,
re-elected to
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/">New Hampshire</a>
House of Representatives.
<li>Jim McClarin, <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/">New Hampshire</a>
House of Representatives.
<li>Dan Gallegos, Regional Transportation District Board, District N, <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/co/">Colorado</a>.
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/M/DavidMorris.html">David Morris</a>,
	Advisory Neighborhood Commission 2F, <a
	href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/dc/">Washington, D.C.</a>
<li>Daniel Walker, Ochlocknee Soil and Water Conservation District Board,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/">Florida</a>.
<li>Dick Bjornseth, Ochlocknee Soil and Water Conservation District Board,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/fl/">Florida</a>.
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/J/TomJamerson.html">Tom Jamerson</a>,
	Chesterfield County Soil and Water Commission,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/va/">Virginia</a>.
<li>Steve Ziegler, Charles County Board of Education,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/md/">Maryland</a>.
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpca/flickinger.html">Bonnie
	Flickinger</a>, re-elected to <a
	href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/MorenoValley.html">Moreno
	Valley</a> City Council,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a>.
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpca/webb.html">Sandi Webb</a>,
	re-elected to the city council of Simi Valley,
	<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a>.
</ul>

<p>Other important electoral events:</p>

<ul>

<li><p>The Libertarian Party won ballot status in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/in/">Indiana</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/mi/">Michigan</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/sd/">South Dakota</a> and
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/wy/">Wyoming</a>,
and maintained it in every state except
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ut/">Utah</a>, bringing the
total to 23 states for 1996 (best showing ever in midterm election).</p></li>

<li><p>Libertarian candidates won 396,000 votes for Congress, 648,000 votes 
for U.S. Senate, and 416,000 for governor.</p></li>

<li><p>Two incumbent Libertarian State Representatives, Andy Borsa and Finlay
Rothhaus, were defeated in New Hampshire.</p></li>

<li><p>Good efforts but losing campaigns: <a
href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpmi/joncoon/index.html">Jon
Coon</a> for U.S. Senate in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/mi/">Michigan</a> won
4.5% of the vote; Guy Wilson for U.S. Congress in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a> (District 37),
in a two-way race against an indicted Democrat, won 21.9%; Terry Savage for
State Assembly in California won 6.9%; <a
href="/revolution/by_name/E/DonErnsberger.html">Don Ernsberger</a> for U.S.
Senate in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/pa/">Pennsylvania</a> won 1.7%;
Mike Hurley for State Representative in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/mo/">Missouri</a> won 23%;
John Reda for State Representative in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/de/">Delaware</a> won 18%;
Scott Kjar for State Assembly in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nv/">Nevada</a> won 6%;
Larry Pratt for State Assembly in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nv/">Nevada</a> won 27%; and Robert
Heitner for Sussex County Freeholder in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nj/">New Jersey</a> won
19%.</p></li>

</ul>

<hr>

<p>Source: <img src="/images/ftp.gif" alt="[FTP]"><a
href="file://ftp.digex.net/pub/access/lphq/releases/election.94.results">
November 12, 1994 news release</a> by the Libertarian Party.</p>

