<head>
<title>1992 Libertarian Campaigns</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>1992 Libertarian Campaigns</h1>

<p>For the 1992 Presidential race, the Libertarian Party nominated
<a href="/revolution/by_name/M/AndreMarrou.html">Andre Marrou</a>
for President and <a href="/revolution/by_name/L/NancyLord.html">Dr. Nancy
Lord</a> for Vice-President. The ticket was on the ballot in all fifty
states plus the District of Columbia and received 291,612 votes.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="ads.html">Television ads tested for effectiveness</a>
<li><a href="marrou.html">Marrou's post-election analysis of campaign</a>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpnh/1992.html">New
	Hampshire elects four Libertarian legislators</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpca/flickinger.html">
	Libertarian elected to city council in California</a></li>
<li><A href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpnv/clark.html">
	Libertarian gets 46% in Nevada state senate race</a></li>
</ul>

